spans.text: There heard confessed the amorous pain Which tore him from his midnight bed
Hymen sooth the bashful maid , She'll wakened , play a softer part
a soft look , a touch , a flower
to her parents bear Thy Lord's designs
that form where speaking grace Gave soul to beauty most refined , The robe of dignity embrace , By taste magnificent designed
Her hair , which floated over her dress , A dress , which to be seen
But the soft curls which haply fell Upon her bosom's heaving snow
her rove Through gaudy halls and rooms of state ; While humble trains at distance wait , And from her nod receive their fate
which such joy Around his aged heart might play
to take a last farewell , Of her more dear then sense or light
to dwell Where filial Julia blessed his sight
the time Which late flew rapid with delight
the time Which late flew rapid with delight
Which late flew rapid with delight
what truth it objects drew , When ruffling zephyr ceased to breathe
Evening's own bird her note enjoyed — When from its shades a soldier sprung
enjoyed — When from its shades a soldier sprung
his beamy eye Bright as fair Julia's own
Strait to each others arms they fly — They mingle joy — they mingle tears
that amid her brilliant state Her heart consuming sorrow nursed
seek our dear paternal plain : From forth my little treasured hoard , Fond tokens to my mother bear
to the beauties of the spot
He grasped in his her trembling hands , He led her forth , but never spoke
— Those piteous shrieks , which tear the ear
the screams of pain , More piercing as they nearer grow
he threw the grating gate : There feast thy loose adulterous eyes , See there , thy paramour's just fate
O , Sister ! plead — then swooned with pain
With eager haste the youth's unbound , And stern Alphonso
the fangs Of deep remorse thy bosom tear
